Event Name: The Art Business Conference New York 2023
Location: 300 Madison Ave Avenue New York NY 10017
Description: The Art Business Conference is a conference for art world professionals in New York. If you are involved in buying, selling or caring for art, whether as a gallery owner, operations director, art advisor, studio manager, foundation, private collector, auctioneer or museum professional, this conference covers the key aspects of running an art business or collection. The conference will also present three industry leading reports together with panel discussions and educational workshops, where industry experts will share specialist advice and insight on the art world - from best practice to the latest updates in legislation and technology. In the Business Pavilion, you can meet speakers and our exhibitors to expand your art business network. For 2023, an additional half day of talks will be introduced on April 27th that will focus on sustainability with workshops and training. The agenda includes discussions on sustainability, art lending, cyber security, and employment in the art world, as well as an art and technology panel. The ticket price includes entry to all sessions, breakfast networking, refreshments, lunch, post-conference networking drinks, and the Day 2 talks. A partner of Turon Travel for accommodation is also available.

Location: ONX Studio 645 5th Avenue Lower Level NY 10022
Description: Join us for the April Lady Tech Guild Meeting, featuring a motion capture tech demo by LaJuné McMillian at ONX Studio. No prior experience necessary! The event is open to women in tech and includes networking, drinks, and snacks. LaJuné is a Multidisciplinary Artist and Educator interested in performance, extended reality, and physical computing. They believe in breaking systems and technologies that perpetuate systemic injustices to create space for different ways of being. LaJuné has presented their work in several venues. ONX Studio, located in the Onassis Gallery in Midtown Manhattan, is a hybrid production and exhibition space that supports interactive and immersive extended reality works. Founded by the Onassis Foundation and New Museum’s NEW INC, ONX is pleased to sponsor women in tech.

Location: 220 E 23rd St East Street Suite 400 New York NY 10010
Description: Join Starta Accelerator's Spring 2023 Pitch Contests in NYC! This event features founders pitching their startups to a panel of VCs, angels, and industry experts, followed by a Q&A and networking session with frontrunners, entrepreneurs, and investors within the NYC startup scene. Refreshments served. Starta is a venture ecosystem supporting early-stage talent in tech seeking professional training, raising capital, and scaling globally. For promo codes, email fc@starta.vc. Check out the cohort startups here: https://starta.vc/spring2023.

Event Name: TECHSPO New York 2023 Technology Expo (Internet ~ AdTech ~ MarTech)
Location: New York Marriott at the Brooklyn Bridge Hotel 333 Adams St NY 11201
Description: TECHSPO New York 2023 is an opportunity for businesses, technology providers, marketers, innovators, and evangelists to come together and showcase the latest advances in technology and innovation. The expo, returning on April 27th and 28th, 2023 to the New York Marriott at the Brooklyn Bridge Hotel, offers a chance to interact with technology enthusiasts, build networks, and reunite with peers. The exhibition hall will showcase the next generation of technology and innovation, including Internet, Mobile, AdTech, MarTech, and SaaS technologies. Attendees will have the opportunity to view presentations that feature Keynotes, Industry Panels, and Master Classes given by Expert Speakers in the digital marketing field. Additionally, there are various event zones, including Auditorium, Exhibition Hall, Training Theater, Podcast Studio, Dining Hall, and Photo Booth, where visitors can interact and enjoy the event. Different passes are offered, including Visitor Pass, Training Pass, and All Access Pass, each with different perks and benefits. Finally, visitors are encouraged to register early, as TECHSPO New York 2023 will sell out quickly. For more details, visit https://techsponyc.com or contact the Customer Service team via info@techspo.co or phone +1 (800) 805-5385 (Toll Free).

Location: Fayerweather Hall Room 513 1180 Amsterdam Avenue New York NY 10027
Description: George Deodatis and Thaddeus Pawlowski will discuss the threat posed by sea level rise and storm-induced flooding to infrastructure, as well as optimal adaptation and mitigation strategies within a budget. Thaddeus will focus on climate adaptation in New York City post-Hurricane Sandy, exploring the need to redesign urban systems that perpetuate social vulnerability. The event is free and open to the public, with registration required. In-person attendees must follow COVID-19 policies and provide proof of vaccination, while online attendees will receive a Zoom link. The event is part of the Climate and Society series, hosted by various organizations including the Center for Science and Society and the Earth Institute. Disability accommodations are available upon request.

Event Name: RevTech Labs, Holt Xchange, and ICBA Present: NYC Fintech Week Top 20
Location: Rise New York 43 West 23rd Street NY 10010
Description: RevTech Labs, Holt Xchange, and ICBA are traveling to New York City to showcase their fintech and insurtech startups on April 27, 2023. The event will feature a pitch competition by the top 20 startups and will be held at Rise NY. Attendees will have the opportunity to network after the event. RevTech Labs is an entrepreneurial hub that operates a 12-week hybrid accelerator program for fintech, insurtech, and healthtech companies. The Holt Xchange is a seed fintech investor based in Canada, while ICBA supports fair competition for financial institutions. Rise is a global community of innovators that operates fintech hubs around the world. Note that the final lineup of startups will be announced later.

Event Name: The Nest Climate Campus, Official Event Partner of Climate Week NYC 2023
Location: Javits Center 445 11th Avenue New York NY 10001
Description: The Nest Climate Campus is a collection of sustainable brands, businesses, individuals, and organizations that aim to accelerate climate solutions through collaboration. Co-hosted events and community engagement activities are held under one green roof at the Javits Center during Climate Week NYC. Attendees can access the Main Stage Summit, which brings together thought-leaders for two days of education, inspiration, and collaboration. Community engagement activities include activations, networking spaces, climate arts, green roof tours, and a plant-based Garden Eatery. Special appearances from influential thought-leaders in New York government and NGOs are also featured. A health and safety policy, as well as photo and video policy and privacy policy, apply to those who register for the event.

Event Name: Out in Tech | We're Tech-nically Dating with Peoplehood
Location: Peoplehood 109 W 17th St New York NY 10011
Description: This event discusses how dating apps have changed the way LGBTQ+ individuals find partners and connect with each other, with almost two-thirds of gay and lesbian couples in the US meeting online. The conversation will focus on creating inclusive spaces for all queer and trans individuals to find love, new technologies for safety, and the factors of privacy and inclusion. Representatives from leading dating companies that are open to the LGBTQ+ community will discuss employees' perspectives on reaching and supporting different segments of the community. The Peoplehood event will have wine and beer available for sale. Priority registration is given to women, trans, gender-expansive, and POC members to ensure diversity. Peoplehood is a guided group conversation practice that helps individuals connect and feel more connected with others. The panelists include Robyn Exton from HER, Marcus Lofthouse from OKCupid, Kel Rakowski from Lex, Adam Cohen-Aslatei from Tawkify, and Michael Kaye from OkCupid. The moderator is Andy Kraut from Grindr. This event is conducted indoors, and attendees are expected to be vaccinated and have tested negative for COVID-19.

Event Name: NY TECH & PROFESSIONAL OUTDOOR NETWORKING EVENT.
Location: Central Park New York NY 11211
Description: This is an outdoor professional networking event where entrepreneurs, techies, founders, and professionals can connect and form partnerships. It is hosted by New York Entrepreneurs, Startup & Business Coalition and the ambiance is business casual. Everyone who attends will be provided with name tags, and light snacks, soda, and water will be served. The event will take place from 1:00 PM to 3:00 PM in Central Park and the exact location will be emailed to registered members one day before the event. Those interested in sponsorship or business queries can contact Moveyourcareer@gmail.com. There is a list of RSVPs in the description as well as social media links for the event.

Location: Alianza Dominicana Cultural Center 530 W 166th St New York NY 10032
Description: This event is for individuals interested in working in technology, regardless of their background or knowledge in coding. The event will feature panel discussions with women from major technology companies such as Google and founders of innovative small technology businesses. Attendees will have the opportunity to network with panel speakers and receive one-on-one mentoring from experts in areas such as marketing and finance. Refreshments will be provided, and donations to support the event are welcome. Women.nyc, part of the New York City Economic Development Corporation, sponsors the program to help women thrive in their careers, run businesses, and launch startups. WE NYC is an initiative to help women start and grow businesses. The event is co-managed by WE Connect, an inclusive innovation agency based in Brooklyn, and NYWIB.

Location: Looking for Host contact partnerships womentech net NYC NY 10001
Description: WomenTech is bringing the community together for an informal meetup in New York City after being apart for two years. The event aims to bring diversity, equality, and a sense of belonging to the tech community. The event is invite-only, with a focus on tech leaders, software engineers, product managers, data, UX & design professionals and other tech roles. While most attendees are women, the event is open to everyone who supports and promotes diversity and inclusion. Different packages are available, including a 10-minute keynote speaking slot, speaker feature on social media, company profile on WomenTech website, logo featured on Global Conference website, and 5 job posts on WomenTech job board. Ask about bundle packages and possibilities for global outreach if interested in involvement in the Women in Tech Global Conference and in-person locations. To host, connect with Anna Radulovski via email at nyc@womentech.net.

Location: Taipei Economic and Cultural Office TECO 1 East 42nd Street New York NY 10017
Description: Join us for the Opening Night of the Human Impacts Institute's Creative Climate Awards (CCA). Enjoy live performances and meet the participating artists of our 2023 CCA. This event is part of the Human Impacts Institute's 2023 Creative Climate Awards, a month-long festival that connects us to climate action for a better world. The festival will run from April 19th - May 12th in NYC. Don't miss this inspiring event packed with innovative ways to address climate change. Learn more by visiting the Human Impacts Institute Creative Climate Awards page: https://www.humanimpactsinstitute.org/cca2023. This event is made possible by our sponsors: New York City Department of Cultural Affairs, Taipei Economic and Cultural Office, Dumbo BID, Queens Botanic Garden, and the New York City DOT Arts Program. See the image below by Mollie Hosmer-Dillard: "The Invention of the Individual".

Event Name: New York Tech Career Fair: Exclusive Tech Hiring Event
Location: Moved to Virtual Event Online New York NY 10119
Description: We are pleased to announce the hosting of a virtual Tech Career Fair where our partnering companies, including fast-growing startups and Fortune 500 technology companies, will be present. We aim to assist these companies in attaining their diversity goals by introducing more diverse candidates to their talent pool. The available roles include Software Engineering, Product Management, Data Scientist, AI/Machine Learning Engineer, Data Analyst, UI/UX Design, Marketing, and Sales. In order to be visible and accessible to hiring partners and companies on the platform, we advise you to complete the sign-up form provided in the link below and upload your resume. Completed and approved profiles will be visible to different companies, which will then invite candidates to a career fair. This is an invite-only event due to the limited number of spaces, and applicants will have to go through an approval process before receiving an invitation. Therefore, it is recommended to create a complete profile and upload a resume to the platform to increase chances of approval. Companies wishing to participate in this event can sign up on the provided link. Please note that companies may sign up for a waitlist if necessary.

Event Name: Responsible Tech Mixer NYC + special guest Douglas Rushkoff! (in-person)
Location: Betaworks 29 Little West 12th Street New York NY 10014
Description: Join us for the Responsible Tech Mixer hosted by All Tech is Human, where people from diverse backgrounds come together to connect, learn and collaborate. Special guest Douglas Rushkoff will be sharing his insights on "Crashing Technosolutionism". Rushkoff, an influential author and documentarian, is known for his work on human autonomy in the digital age. During the mixer, there will be a giveaway of his recent book, Survival of the Richest. All Tech is Human is a non-profit organization committed to addressing complex tech & society issues and building a responsible tech future aligning with public interests. They have various activities including building a mentorship program, hosting mixers, summits, and livestreams. You can get involved by joining their Slack community or by exploring their job board and talent pool. If you're interested in Responsible Tech, join us at the mixer in NYC on April 26th.

Event Name: Women in Climate Investing & Finance - Being Green by Investing Green
Location: Norton Rose Fulbright 1301 6th Avenue New York NY 10019
Description: Join Women in Climate Investing & Finance for an evening of cocktails and connection, aimed at building a community of empowered women working together to fight climate change. The event is ideal for those in clean and renewable energy investing, sustainable energy and infrastructure, climate tech, energy transition and ESG. To sign up for the event in advance, please use the link provided. There is a 20% discount code available. The agenda includes check-in and networking, welcome remarks from several organizations, and small group networking. Refreshments and light appetizers will be provided by Norton Rose Fulbright, who are co-hosting the event with several sponsors. Women in Climate Investing & Finance exists to provide a space for women to connect and support each other within climate investing and finance. All attendees are welcome, even if new to the field. Connect with Women in Climate Investing & Finance on LinkedIn, Twitter, and Instagram. Note that the organization reserves the right to use any photograph or video taken at the event without explicit permission.

Location: City Tech New Academic Building 285 Jay Street Brooklyn NY 11201
Description: The event titled "Good Trouble: Creativity + Collaboration" will feature architects, academics, and change makers who will explore solutions to pressing problems in the built environment while using the AIA framework for design excellence as an anchor. The event will focus on sustainability, inclusivity, and resilience in the borough, city, and beyond. It is an in-person program that will include refreshments and will start promptly at 6 PM. The event is sponsored by KPF and Henning Larsen, and it is open to AIA Brooklyn members, City Tech students and faculty, and NYC residents. Visitors to the City Tech campus must provide proof of full vaccination or a negative COVID-19 PCR test performed by an accredited lab no more than 7 days prior to the visit. The event will occur every third Wednesday of the month, and upcoming events will focus on Design for Integration and Design for Ecosystems. Past events have explored Design for Energy, Design for Change, and Design for Water.

Location: Sour Mouse 110 Delancey Street New York NY 10002
Description: This is an invitation to attend a networking mixer in the startup space called Startup+. The event is open to tech founders, SaaS founders, entrepreneurs, recruiters, freelancers, startup mentors, coaches, and engineers. The aim is to connect with like-minded individuals and organizations in the startup ecosystem. The event will be an excellent opportunity to make new connections, share ideas, and learn from the experiences of others. Attendees can network with potential investors, customers, partners, and mentors. The dress code is business casual, and attendees are advised to bring their business cards as name tags will be provided. Photos and videos taken during the event may be used to promote future events. Register now to secure your spot.

Location: Norton Rose Fulbright 1301 6th Avenue New York NY 10019
Description: This event is for informational purposes and tickets can be obtained by clicking on the provided link. It is important to note that both speakers and agenda may be subject to changes. The event has been co-produced by Financial Poise Productions, ReFED, Tech Up for Women, Women in Climate Investing and Finance, Women + in Climate Tech, and Women of Renewable Industries and Sustainable Energy (WRISE). Additionally, the NYC Metro Chapter of the Private Directors Association and Private Director Symposium have been listed as associate producers. Interested parties looking to become an associate producer for the event are advised to email info@financialpoise.com.

Event Name: NY FinTech Week: Accelerating the Adoption of Climate Technologies
Location: 75 Greene St Street Floor 2 New York NY 10012
Description: Join Tenet for a happy hour networking event and discussion during NYC FinTech Week. Meet other climate fintech companies and listen to Alex Liegl, CEO of Tenet, and XXX of New York Green Bank during a discussion moderated by Auto Finance News' Joey Pizzolato. Together, we will discuss "Building Digital Financial Infrastructure to Make EVs More Affordable" and "Using Fintech to Leverage Public and Private Capital to Catalyze Decarbonization." This event will be hosted at Tenet’s SoHo office space.

Event Name: Climate, Tech & Society: A Fireside with Chante Harris and Stephan Nicoleau
Location: Verizon Executive Education Center 2 West Loop Road New York NY 10044
Description:
Join us for a fireside chat with Chante Harris and Stephan Nicoleau, who are leaders in social and financial innovation around climate technology at SecondMUSE and FullCycle respectively. The event will be moderated by Michael Samuelian, Director of the Urban Tech Hub at Cornell Tech. The talk will be live-streamed, but if you wish to attend in person, please reserve a spot through the attached RSVP link. The Zoom live stream link is also available. The event includes a fireside chat, followed by Q&A, refreshments, and networking opportunities. 

Chante Harris is a champion of social and financial innovation and has successfully scaled nationwide campaigns, technologies, and ideas for various organizations, including the Obama Administration, Fortune 500 companies, and startups. She has spent the last two years leading climate investment and partnerships at SecondMUSE, sourcing, funding, and scaling the best early-stage climate tech solutions across the globe. Chante is also the co-founder of Women of Color Collective in Sustainability (WOC/CS), a global digital collective and community dedicated to advancing women of color working in the sustainability industry.

Stephan Nicoleau is a General Partner at FullCycle, a sustainable infrastructure fund that is accelerating climate solutions globally. He represents FullCycle within GFANZ - the Glasgow Financial Alliance for Net Zero - and serves on the board of Project Drawdown and other organizations. He is a noted thought leader among investors in the climate and infrastructure sectors and frequently speaks on topics related to climate, innovation, finance, and policy. 

The event is a great opportunity to gain insights into climate technology and sustainability from two leaders in the industry.

Location: 275 Park Ave Avenue Brooklyn NY 11205
Description: Join us for a night of comedy at 275 Park as we kick off the Spring season. Hosted by Chris Grant and Ray Dejon, this event features some of the funniest comedians in the city. Chris also hosts a monthly show downtown where comics practice their craft in preparation for big shows like this one. Don't miss out on this limited seating event, get your tickets now. Here's what to expect: patrons will be seated and servers will take orders while music plays. Then, the DJ will warm up the crowd for approximately 30 minutes before Chris Grant opens the show. Three comics will perform, each for 15 minutes, with a host break in between during which CFU will interact with the audience and servers will drop checks. The show concludes with the closer.

Event Name: Silicon Alley NYC Startup & Tech Mixer
Location: 5th Mad 7 East 36th Street New York NY 10016
Description: Get ready for an exciting opportunity to network with some of the most successful companies in NYC! This premier tech networking event has one of the largest membership groups in Southern California and is growing every month. Meet potential clients, find your next job, start a conversation with a new cofounder, make new friends, and get some great advice from the founder. The event will take place from 6:00-9:00PM, and guests can enjoy drinks while mingling with top companies and top talent in the industry. Past attendees have included Google, Sony, Electronic Arts, Hulu, and many others. Social Proof is a professional networking group in Los Angeles that focuses on tech, startups, and entrepreneurship, and their goal is to connect people through networking events, online networking events, and summits. Enjoy the most successful Startup & Tech Mixer in NYC and mingle with highly successful men and women in the startup, tech, and entrepreneurial space. This event is an opportunity to forge strong, lasting relationships within the Silicon Beach community, combining Fortune 500/1000s with Entrepreneurs and Startups. The event includes a cash bar, and there are no refunds, substitutions, or exchanges once tickets are purchased. If you can't make it to this event, contact the organizers for free access to the next one. Please note, companies who sponsor events or billboards are not guaranteed to be present, and food and drinks are not provided for free because the organizers are a startup networking organization focused on making lasting offline connections.

Location: Online
Description: This event is for founders looking for connections in the climate tech space, including co-founders, strategic partnerships, and advice from peers. It is aimed at early-stage to Series A founders and will be held every two weeks. Each session will involve two founders presenting their startups and challenges, followed by separate break-out room discussions where founders can discuss their win of the week, challenge of the week, and question to the group. There will also be networking roulette to connect with other group members. Upon registration, attendees will receive a login link via email. Startup Basecamp's events are open to everyone and attendees are encouraged to review event etiquette before attending. Interested individuals can also join Startup Basecamp.

Location: İzQ İnovasyon Merkezi No 126 Atatürk Caddesi İzmir 35210 Turkey
Description: The Climate Tech Community is a community that aims to bring together professionals, entrepreneurs, academics, and young people who are interested in developing technology-based solutions for one of today's most important problems, "climate change". The community has several working areas such as community meetings, a dataset of technology-based solutions for climate change and sustainability, a knowledge pool of reports, educational articles, and content for entrepreneurs and sustainability enthusiasts, acceleration programs, and a platform for interaction between firms, working entrepreneurs and investors in the field. The agenda has four main events including a welcome address, an introduction to the Climate Tech Community, a presentation on why we talk about climate technologies in 2023, and speeches from entrepreneurs. There will also be a coffee break and a closing networking session.
